  simp [Nat.ModEq, mul_mod]
```

The third property states that each limb of the result `r` is less than $2^{52}$. We need to verify that the result of `mul_mod p lhs rhs` has each limb less than $2^{52}$.

When multiplying two numbers in $\mathbb{Z}/p\mathbb{Z}$, the result is computed as $(a \cdot b) \bmod p$. The result of this operation is a natural number less than $p$. 

We need to show that when this result is represented as an array of 5 natural numbers (limbs), each limb is less than $2^{52}$. 

A natural number less than $p = 2^{255} - 19$ can be represented as a 5-tuple of natural numbers where each is less than $2^{51}$ (since $5 \cdot 51 = 255$). In fact, the result of `mul_mod p lhs rhs` is a natural number less than $p$, so when represented as 5 limbs, each will be less than $2^{51}$ (and hence less than $2^{52}$).

