```

We need to show that the `i`-th limb of the product `mul lhs rhs` is less than `2^52`.

The computation of `mul` involves polynomial multiplication followed by reduction modulo `p`. The resulting element will have limbs that are computed from the product of the inputs, effectively performing the multiplication in `GF(p)`.

We can use the fact that `mul` is defined to produce an element in `GF(p)`, and the natural embedding of `GF(p)` into `Z/pZ` preserves the structure.

